{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","text":"PID File Lifecycle","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" detects stale PID files by checking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","title":"PIDFile"},"abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"generated":true},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/docum